\newlabel{fig:speedup}{{5}{10}{Time per simulation (log scale). Numba JIT delivers a $\mathbf {1868\times }$ speedup over pure Python. The trained FNO is expected to be a further $\sim 17\times $ faster than Numba on CPU, and $\sim 1000\times $ faster on GPU — giving a total speedup of $>10^5$ vs.\ the original Python}{figure.caption.12}{}}
